(*                                                                           *)
(* Two things first appear here, past HEAD4, both verified vs the binary:    *)
(*  - the round-4..7 register rotation continues the period-8 cycle;         *)
(*  - the K-table address uses the DOUBLED-ROW stride: round t reads K from  *)
(*    kbase + 32*(t DIV 4) + 4*(t MOD 4) (a +20 lea after every 4th round),  *)
(*    so k4..k7 sit at kbase+32/+36/+40/+44, NOT kbase+16.. (the naive 4*t). *)
(*    The kbase nonoverlapping span is correspondingly 48 = rbp_off 7 + 4,   *)
(*    wide enough to preserve every carried K read across the W-ring stores. *)
