(*                                                                           *)
(* HEAD8 scaled to all 16 head rounds (15 inline ENSURES_SEQUENCE_TAC cuts at *)
(* pc+194/+299/.../+1663), mechanically generated by                          *)
(* orchestrator/logs/session-007-gen.py (its N=4 output is token-identical to *)
(* the hand-written HEAD4 above - regression-checked).  After 16 rounds the   *)
(* period-8 register rotation realigns to canonical (a->RAX,..,h->R11), the   *)
(* clean seam into rounds_16_xx.                                             *)
(*                                                                           *)
(* ROUND-15 DEFERRED Sigma0 FOLD (verified vs the binary).  Round 15 defers   *)
(* its  add %r14d,%eax  (Sigma0 fold completing new-a) PAST the head-exit JMP  *)
(* at pc+1764: the JMP is at orig 0x6e8, the fold at orig 0x6fb = pc+1783.    *)
(* So at pc+1764 RAX would hold only T1+Maj and R14 the Sigma0 addend - a     *)
(* SPLIT new-a.  To land on a clean compress-16 state we step the final       *)
(* segment 37 instrs to pc+1786 (just past the fold), absorbing it into RAX.  *)
(* Between pc+1764 and pc+1786 the 16_xx prologue only loads W[1]/W[14] into   *)
(* scratch r13/r15 and rotates them; R14 (=Sigma0) is preserved across the    *)
